## PitchTrailEngine

**File:** `js/engines/pitchTrailEngine.js`  
**Purpose:** Scrolling pitch-history trail with C-note grid, register-coloured line, and challenge mode (target note + tolerance zone).

### Constructor

```js
const trail = new PitchTrailEngine(canvasElement, options?);
```

| Option | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `pitchMin` | `36` | MIDI C2 — bottom of display range |
| `pitchMax` | `84` | MIDI C6 — top of display range |
| `pxPerFrame` | `2` | Horizontal scroll speed (pixels per `frame()` call) |
| `lineWidth` | `2.5` | Trail stroke width in CSS pixels |
| `dotRadius` | `5` | Radius of the "current note" glowing dot |
| `toleranceST` | `1.0` | ±semitones tolerance for challenge hit detection |

### Methods

| Method | Signature | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `frame(midi)` | `frame(number \| NaN)` | Feed one MIDI note. `NaN` = silence gap (draws nothing, scrolls). Call every animation frame during recording. |
| `setTarget(midi)` | `setTarget(number \| null)` | Set the challenge target note. `null` clears it. |
| `getAccuracy()` | `→ { isHit, semitones }` | Returns current pitch accuracy vs. target. |
| `reset()` | `reset()` | Clears buffer and trail. Call on recording start. |

### Visual Anatomy

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ C5 · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · ·  │  ← faint grid
│                                                    ╭─────●    │  ← trail + dot
│ C4 · · · · · · · · · · · ·· (TARGET ─────────────)· · · · ·  │  ← C4 cyan grid
│                  ╭─────────╯  ← tolerance zone   ╰───────    │
│ C3 · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · · ·  │
│←─ left-fade ─→  ←──── circular buffer scrolls right ────→ •  │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Trail Colour by Register

The trail colour shifts based on the current note's register:

| Register | MIDI range | Trail colour |
|---|---|---|
| Bass | < C3 (48) | `#6b3fa0` Deep Violet |
| Baritone/Tenor | C3–B3 (48–59) | `#b6a0ff` Electric Violet (primary) |
| Alto/Mezzo | C4–B4 (60–71) | `#00d4e8` Cyan-Violet blend |
| Soprano | ≥ C5 (72) | `#00f1fe` Cyan Glow |

In challenge mode, when the pitch is **within ±toleranceST of the target**: trail colour → `#ffe792` (Gold).

### Challenge Mode

```js
// Arena: set target note (e.g. play scale exercise)
trail.setTarget(60);  // C4

// Each frame during recording:
trail.frame(detectedMidi);

// Query accuracy:
const { isHit, semitones } = trail.getAccuracy();
// isHit:     boolean — true if within ±1 semitone
// semitones: number  — absolute distance from target (or NaN if no pitch)
```

The engine draws:
- **Target line** — dashed horizontal at the target MIDI note
- **Tolerance band** — semi-transparent gold zone ± `toleranceST` semitones above/below
- **Gold trail** — when pitch is within tolerance, line turns gold and glows

### Grid Lines

C-note grid lines are drawn at C2–C6, filtered to only those within `pitchMin`–`pitchMax`.  
C4 (Middle C) is highlighted in cyan; others are faint violet.

| Note | From top (C2–C6 range) | Colour |
|---|---|---|
| C5 | 25% | `rgba(182,160,255, 0.10)` faint violet |
| C4 | 50% | `rgba(0,241,254, 0.18)` cyan — Middle C |
| C3 | 75% | `rgba(182,160,255, 0.10)` faint violet |

### Circular Buffer

Trail data is stored in a circular buffer of length `Math.ceil(canvasWidth / pxPerFrame)`.  
Each slot stores a MIDI note (or `NaN` for silence). On each `frame()` call, the oldest value is overwritten and all slots are redrawn left-to-right.

### Tuning Parameters

| Parameter | Value | Effect if increased | Effect if decreased |
|---|---|---|---|
| `pxPerFrame` | `2` | Trail scrolls faster, shorter history | Slower scroll, longer history visible |
| `lineWidth` | `2.5` | Thicker trail | Thinner trail |
| `dotRadius` | `5` | Larger live-note indicator | Smaller indicator |
| `toleranceST` | `1.0` | Easier challenge hit detection | Stricter (requires near-perfect pitch) |

