## Integration in `studio.js`

```js
import { LevelEngine     } from '../engines/levelEngine.js';
import { PitchTrailEngine } from '../engines/pitchTrailEngine.js';

// Instantiate once per render()
const levelEngine = new LevelEngine($('levelCanvas'));
const trailEngine = new PitchTrailEngine($('pitchTrailCanvas'), {
    pitchMin: PITCH_MIN,   // 36 = C2
    pitchMax: PITCH_MAX,   // 84 = C6
});

// On recording start:
levelEngine.reset();
trailEngine.reset();

// Each animation frame (inside updatePitch()):
levelEngine.frame(rms);
trailEngine.frame(trailMidi);    // NaN if no clear pitch / below RMS gate

// On stop:
// Engines stop receiving frames — canvas retains last drawn state
```

### Canvas HTML

```html
<!-- Trail — persistent, visible idle and during recording -->
<div class="trail-wrap">
    <canvas id="pitchTrailCanvas" aria-label="Pitch history trail"></canvas>
</div>

<!-- Level — shown only during recording (hidden class toggled by JS) -->
<div id="levelSection" class="level-section hidden">
    <p class="section-label">Signal Level</p>
    <div class="level-track">
        <canvas id="levelCanvas" aria-label="Signal level meter"></canvas>
    </div>
</div>
```

### CSS Sizing

Both canvases are sized `width: 100%; height: 100%` via CSS, with the parent container defining the height:

```css
.trail-wrap  { height: 160px; }
.level-track { height: 8px; }
```

Engines use `getBoundingClientRect()` at first frame for DPR-aware internal resolution.

